definitions.definition: ( intransitive ) To endure , continue over time.
examples: Summer seems to last longer each year.
They seem happy now, but that won't last long.

definitions.definition: ( intransitive ) To hold out, continue undefeated or entire.
examples: I don't know how much longer we can last without reinforcements.

definitions.definition: ( intransitive , slang , of a man ) To purposefully refrain from orgasm
( transitive , obsolete ) To perform , carry out .

definitions.definition: To shape with a last; to fasten or fit to a last; to place smoothly on a last.
